94
00:05:43,179 --> 00:05:45,360
Why? What about me?

95
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:48,060
It's exasperating.

96
00:05:53,498 --> 00:05:54,998
Come here.

97
00:06:30,637 --> 00:06:33,267
Let me wash your face in return.

98
00:06:45,664 --> 00:06:48,420
Taking turns is good, isn't it?

99
00:06:48,420 --> 00:06:51,373
You wash my face. I wash yours.

100
00:06:51,373 --> 00:06:53,592
If we wash our own face, it might not be clean enough.

101
00:06:53,592 --> 00:06:56,470
We could get acne. Don't you think?

102
00:06:59,981 --> 00:07:01,773
Or should I leave it like this?

103
00:07:01,773 --> 00:07:05,074
You look cute with the whiskers.

104
00:07:05,074 --> 00:07:07,974
I also look cute without the whiskers.

105
00:07:14,058 --> 00:07:19,412
Oh, but I don't think I can wash that redness off your face now.

106
00:07:24,366 --> 00:07:28,725
I should thank Jigsaw for giving us a chance to spend time together

107
00:07:28,725 --> 00:07:31,166
even after our mission is complete.

108
00:07:31,795 --> 00:07:34,251
You'll be thanking him for a long time.

109
00:07:39,101 --> 00:07:41,074
Two teaspoons.

110
00:07:42,758 --> 00:07:44,617
How many?

111
00:07:44,617 --> 00:07:46,417
180.

112
00:07:49,966 --> 00:07:52,182
Jigsaw can drink this.

113
00:07:54,667 --> 00:07:56,723
Puen!

114
00:08:06,093 --> 00:08:07,772
This one?

115
00:08:07,772 --> 00:08:09,472
Okay.

116
00:08:18,066 --> 00:08:19,066
Hey.

117
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:23,559
I'll start looking for you now.

118
00:08:27,793 --> 00:08:29,575
- Hey, Puen.
- Hmm?

119
00:08:29,575 --> 00:08:31,389
Have you seen Jigsaw?

120
00:08:37,758 --> 00:08:39,358
No.

121
00:08:40,483 --> 00:08:42,358
Jigsaw.

122
00:08:52,796 --> 00:08:54,596
Jigsaw!

123
00:08:56,351 --> 00:08:59,360
Papa, let's play!

124
00:09:09,725 --> 00:09:12,303
Is it out yet?

125
00:09:13,951 --> 00:09:15,851
Push.

126
00:09:42,478 --> 00:09:45,064
- Is it out?
- It's out.

127
00:09:46,409 --> 00:09:48,209
High five.

128
00:10:09,300 --> 00:10:11,440
I should really thank Jigsaw

129
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:15,980
for giving Puen and me another chance to share the same goal,

130
00:10:15,989 --> 00:10:19,720
which is to make this unfamiliar kid

131
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:22,820
the happiest to be with us.

132
00:11:19,624 --> 00:11:27,157
May you fall in love with me.

133
00:11:34,179 --> 00:11:36,067
- Puen.
- Hmm?

134
00:11:36,067 --> 00:11:41,345
Do you think Jigsaw has more dolls now than his first day?

135
00:11:41,345 --> 00:11:43,772
I don't think so.

136
00:11:43,772 --> 00:11:47,515
I've never seen that shark.

137
00:11:51,995 --> 00:11:54,264
Jigsaw.

138
00:11:54,264 --> 00:11:56,903
Where did you get that shark?

139
00:12:04,702 --> 00:12:06,272
Whoa. This room is full of animals.

140
00:12:06,272 --> 00:12:10,465
Do you want to go to the zoo tomorrow, Jigsaw?

141
00:12:10,465 --> 00:12:12,478
- Do you want to go?
- Yes.

142
00:12:12,478 --> 00:12:14,997
Yay!

143
00:12:14,997 --> 00:12:18,082
- We're going to the zoo.
- Wait.

144
00:12:18,082 --> 00:12:20,386
I have to submit my work tomorrow.

145
00:12:22,823 --> 00:12:24,675
But it's okay.

146
00:12:27,590 --> 00:12:29,001
I can reschedule.

147
00:12:29,001 --> 00:12:31,706
Yay!

148
00:12:31,706 --> 00:12:33,995
Let's fly!

149
00:12:34,971 --> 00:12:37,003
What do you want to see tomorrow?

150
00:12:37,003 --> 00:12:38,787
- What do you want to see tomorrow?
- Giraffes.

151
00:12:38,787 --> 00:12:41,416
Giraffes? You want to see the giraffes?

152
00:12:41,416 --> 00:12:43,955
What do giraffes look like?

153
00:12:43,955 --> 00:12:45,320
What else do you want to see? Birds?

154
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:47,340
Let's fly. Woo!

155
00:12:51,517 --> 00:12:54,076
How do birds fly?

156
00:12:58,598 --> 00:13:00,236
- Hat?
- Ready.

157
00:13:00,236 --> 00:13:01,831
- Binoculars?
- Ready.

158
00:13:01,831 --> 00:13:03,776
- Drink?
- Ready.

159
00:13:03,776 --> 00:13:05,767
If we're ready...

160
00:13:05,767 --> 00:13:09,538
Let's go!

161
00:13:10,358 --> 00:13:11,826
Go!

162
00:13:11,826 --> 00:13:13,953
Careful.

163
00:13:30,144 --> 00:13:32,068
Hippo!

164
00:13:32,068 --> 00:13:34,490
Wait for it to open its mouth.

165
00:13:34,490 --> 00:13:36,119
Go.

166
00:13:36,119 --> 00:13:38,119
Throw it over.

167
00:13:42,335 --> 00:13:44,897
Hippo.

168
00:13:47,440 --> 00:13:50,490
It's your turn to rest.

169
00:13:50,490 --> 00:13:51,820
- That one?
- Pork leg.

170
00:13:51,820 --> 00:13:53,930
Whoa. Pork leg?

171
00:13:59,014 --> 00:14:01,360
One, two, three.

172
00:14:31,006 --> 00:14:33,452
You should take a break.

173
00:14:43,451 --> 00:14:45,638
Now I feel refreshed.

174
00:14:51,168 --> 00:14:53,800
Can you hold this and watch Jigsaw?

175
00:14:54,897 --> 00:14:56,639
Hello.

176
00:15:01,082 --> 00:15:02,917
Do you like it?

177
00:15:07,570 --> 00:15:09,270
Puen.

178
00:15:10,546 --> 00:15:12,657
Can you hold this for a second?

179
00:15:12,657 --> 00:15:14,723
Thank you.

180
00:15:17,499 --> 00:15:18,409
Hello.

181
00:15:18,409 --> 00:15:22,283
I don't think I can. I'm outside.

182
00:15:25,401 --> 00:15:27,500
I'll hurry back and finish it.

183
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:29,890
I think I can get it done this evening.

184
00:15:32,488 --> 00:15:35,983
My house is next to a forest.

185
00:15:38,475 --> 00:15:41,375
I'll submit it as soon as I can.

186
00:15:43,276 --> 00:15:45,378
I'll call you back in a minute.

187
00:15:45,378 --> 00:15:47,399
Okay. Bye.

188
00:15:51,155 --> 00:15:52,500
Shit.

189
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:53,587
Where's Jigsaw?

190
00:15:53,587 --> 00:15:55,912
I want to ask you the same thing.

191
00:15:56,683 --> 00:15:58,687
- Jigsaw!
- Jigsaw!

192
00:15:58,687 --> 00:16:00,041
Jigsaw!

193
00:16:00,041 --> 00:16:01,641
Jigsaw!

194
00:16:03,908 --> 00:16:05,385
Jigsaw!

195
00:16:05,385 --> 00:16:06,748
Jigsaw!

196
00:16:06,748 --> 00:16:09,625
What are you guys looking for?

197
00:16:09,625 --> 00:16:11,225
Jigsaw!

198
00:16:19,412 --> 00:16:20,731
Are you all right?

199
00:16:20,731 --> 00:16:22,944
Do you have bruises anywhere?

200
00:16:25,156 --> 00:16:26,841
What brings you guys here?

201
00:16:26,841 --> 00:16:31,541
We saw your stories, so we followed.

202
00:16:31,541 --> 00:16:34,949
When we arrived, we saw your kid feeding a monkey over there.

203
00:16:34,949 --> 00:16:37,387
He probably found a friend.

204
00:16:37,387 --> 00:16:39,315
It's my fault.

205
00:16:40,177 --> 00:16:42,801
I'm sorry, Jigsaw.

206
00:16:58,601 --> 00:17:00,401
Jigsaw.

207
00:17:05,133 --> 00:17:07,281
I'm sorry.

208
00:17:07,281 --> 00:17:11,640
If next time all I do is work, you can tell me off,

209
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:13,960
but please don't disappear like that again.

210
00:17:16,417 --> 00:17:18,509
Okay.

211
00:17:18,509 --> 00:17:20,940
Let's go poopoo.

212
00:17:28,408 --> 00:17:32,486
How did Jigsaw end up with you guys at the zoo?

213
00:17:32,486 --> 00:17:35,410
Their two papas were busy talking on their phones.

214
00:17:35,410 --> 00:17:38,605
When he saw us, we quickly ran to him.

215
00:17:38,605 --> 00:17:40,220
We didn't know what to do.

216
00:17:40,220 --> 00:17:42,550
We were afraid the truth would come out.

217
00:17:46,774 --> 00:17:49,387
I think we should end this plan.

218
00:17:51,019 --> 00:17:55,416
You must've been missing Jigsaw badly, right, Tup?

219
00:17:57,216 --> 00:18:02,880
I'm scared my sister will scold me for doing this to her kid.

220
00:18:02,880 --> 00:18:05,800
I'll come to see you every day, Jigsaw.

221
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:07,570
Don't be afraid.

222
00:18:07,570 --> 00:18:10,397
If we come every day, they'll become suspicious.

223
00:18:10,397 --> 00:18:12,815
Listen to Uncle Two, Jigsaw.

224
00:18:12,815 --> 00:18:15,288
You're the hero of this game.

225
00:18:15,288 --> 00:18:21,621
If you do as I say, I'll bring you a doll every day. Okay?

226
00:18:22,324 --> 00:18:25,631
But first, tell me what you have to call the owners of this house.

227
00:18:25,631 --> 00:18:28,587
- Papa.
- That's correct. It's yours.

228
00:18:28,587 --> 00:18:29,776
Hey.

229
00:18:29,776 --> 00:18:30,802
- Now?
- Yes.

230
00:18:30,802 --> 00:18:32,612
Let's go.

231
00:18:32,612 --> 00:18:35,363
That's right, Jigsaw. Yes.

232
00:18:36,046 --> 00:18:37,946
Let's go.

233
00:18:44,477 --> 00:18:46,863
Papa.

234
00:18:46,863 --> 00:18:52,019
Thank you so much for bringing Jigsaw to us that night.

235
00:18:54,100 --> 00:18:58,063
It seems you guys are happy and things are going well.

236
00:19:02,550 --> 00:19:04,810
But I feel guilty about doing this to Talay.

237
00:19:05,822 --> 00:19:08,735
It's like I'm lying to him.

238
00:19:08,735 --> 00:19:10,935
I'll report this to the police.

239
00:19:10,935 --> 00:19:13,808
You two stay and work with Talay here.

240
00:19:13,808 --> 00:19:16,933
I think you can't handle that alone.

241
00:19:16,933 --> 00:19:20,128
Let Tup go with you, in case the kid gets naughty.

242
00:19:20,128 --> 00:19:22,277
That sounds good.

243
00:19:23,656 --> 00:19:25,156
Go.

244
00:19:32,829 --> 00:19:34,329
Puen.

245
00:19:35,514 --> 00:19:39,350
Jigsaw is my nephew.

246
00:19:39,350 --> 00:19:40,850
What?

247
00:19:40,850 --> 00:19:42,793
Please listen to my reason first.

248
00:19:42,793 --> 00:19:45,407
Two saw that you guys have been fighting lately,

249
00:19:45,407 --> 00:19:49,321
